sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/CI
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as kuberay-operator<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>6379,8265,10001/TCP
    participant Autoscaler as Ray Autoscaler<br/>Sidecar
    participant WorkerPod as Ray Worker Pod
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Metrics Scraper
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,WorkerPod: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation and Lifecycle Management

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f raycluster.yaml<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch Event: RayCluster Created<br/>TLS 1.2+ ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod, Services<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
    K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull Ray image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ Pull Secret
    Registry-->>K8sAPI: Ray container image
    K8sAPI-->>HeadPod: Start Ray Head (GCS, Dashboard)

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>WorkerPod: Start Ray Worker
    WorkerPod->>HeadPod: Register with GCS<br/>6379/TCP Redis None/None

    Autoscaler->>HeadPod: Query cluster state<br/>6379/TCP Redis None/None
    Autoscaler->>K8sAPI: Scale Worker Pods<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token

    Prometheus->>Operator: Scrape /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP None/None

    Note over User,Client: Flow 2: RayJob Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f rayjob.yaml<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch Event: RayJob Created<br/>TLS 1.2+ ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster for job<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
    Note over K8sAPI,WorkerPod: (RayCluster provisioned as above)

    Operator->>HeadPod: Submit job via Dashboard API<br/>8265/TCP HTTP Optional-TLS/None
    HeadPod->>HeadPod: Schedule job via GCS<br/>6379/TCP Redis Internal
    HeadPod-->>WorkerPod: Execute distributed tasks<br/>Ray Protocol
    WorkerPod-->>HeadPod: Return results
    HeadPod-->>Operator: Job completion status<br/>8265/TCP HTTP Optional-TLS/None
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update RayJob status<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Cleanup RayCluster (optional)<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token

    Note over User,Client: Flow 3: RayService Model Serving

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f rayservice.yaml<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch Event: RayService Created<br/>TLS 1.2+ ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster + Serve Service<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
    Operator->>HeadPod: Deploy Ray Serve application<br/>8265/TCP HTTP Optional-TLS/None
    Operator->>HeadPod: Health check Ray Serve<br/>8000/TCP HTTP Optional-TLS/None
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route/Ingress<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token

    Client->>Route: POST /predict<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3 App-defined
    Route->>HeadPod: Forward to Ray Serve<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS Optional-TLS/App-defined
    HeadPod->>WorkerPod: Distribute inference workload<br/>Ray Protocol
    WorkerPod-->>HeadPod: Inference result
    HeadPod-->>Route: JSON response
    Route-->>Client: HTTPS response TLS1.3

    Note over Operator,Client: Zero-downtime upgrade flow
    User->>K8sAPI: Update RayService spec<br/>Auth: User credentials
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create new RayCluster<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
    Operator->>HeadPod: Health check new cluster<br/>8000/TCP HTTP Optional-TLS/None
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update Service endpoint to new cluster<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Delete old RayCluster<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ SA Token
